         <entryFree xml:id="k000139" type="architectural feature">
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-1" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin-nt" type="preferred">pingliang</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-2" xml:lang="zh-Hant">平梁</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-3" xml:lang="zh-Hans">平梁</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-4" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin" source="#biblk000139-1">píngliáng</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-5" xml:lang="zh-latn-wadegile">p'ing-liang</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-6" xml:lang="en" type="literal_translation" source="#biblk000139-2">level, flat; even;roofbeam, ridgepole (lit.)</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-7" xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000139-3">top beam</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-8" xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000139-4">two-rafter crossbeam</term>
            <note type="Gloss">
               <p xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000139-5">literally: level or leveling beam, this is the top beam or upper-most beam in a roof frame (Guo 2002, 62; Zuo 2019, 177)</p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000139-5">木構梁架中最上層的梁。</p>
            </note>
            <note type="Note (brief)">
               <p xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000139-6">Pingliang refers to cross beams that span two rafters and are located on the highest layer of the roof frame. This term is used in the <term ref="https://tinyurl.com/36hnkkzs">Yingzao Fashi</term>, where it is also called pingfu 平栿. In extant architecture, shuzhu 蜀柱 and chashou 叉手 are joined into the top of the pingliang (Liang 1983, 142; Chen 2010, 114). In official Qing dynasty architectural terminology, the beam in the location of the pingliang is called sanjialiang 三架梁, meaning a beam that spans three purlins (and two rafters), or taipingliang 太平梁.</p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000139-6">平梁為《營造法式》（1103）所用術語，也稱平栿。指長兩椽，位於梁架最上一層的梁。現存實例中平梁上通常立蜀柱與叉手（梁1983, 142；陳2010，114）。在清官式的梁架及其術語體系中，屋架最上層的太平梁或三架梁與《营造法式》平梁相當。</p>
            </note>            
